** May 11, 2026 - May 17, 2026
REDACTED NAME (REDACTED COMPANY)

REDACTED-TENANT-ID

** Major updates
----------------
Security Detection Report in Teams Admin Center

MC1311977 | May 15 - A new Security Detection Report in the Teams admin cen=
ter offers centralized visibility into messaging threats like impersonation=
, malicious URLs, and unsafe files. Available from late June 2026, it helps=
 admins investigate, export data, and block malicious users, enhancing secu=
rity operations and response workflows.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11977?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

(Updated) Microsoft Teams: AI meeting recap without transcript to meet comp=
liance policies

MC1275312 | May 14 - Microsoft Teams will offer AI meeting recaps without s=
aving transcripts or recordings, supporting compliance policies. Available =
mid-2026 for M365 Copilot Premium users, admins control AI features tenant-=
wide, and organizers can enable/disable recaps before or during meetings. S=
ummaries are stored temporarily in OneDrive.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC12=
75312?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Microsoft SharePoint: Retirement of IDCRL authentication protocol and enfor=
cement of OpenID Connect and OAuth protocols

MC1184649 | May 13 - Microsoft is retiring the legacy IDCRL authentication =
protocol in SharePoint Online and OneDrive for Business by May 1, 2026, enf=
orcing modern protocols OpenID Connect and OAuth. Legacy authentication wil=
l be blocked starting February 16, 2026, with temporary re-enablement until=
 April 30, 2026. Organizations must migrate promptly.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC11=
84649?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Action required: Upgrade macOS 13 devices to maintain Teams desktop access

MC1308857 | May 12 - Microsoft Teams will stop desktop client updates for m=
acOS 13 starting May 2026, with upgrade notifications in June and blocking =
access by mid-July. Users must upgrade macOS or use Teams on the web. Organ=
izations should identify affected devices, plan upgrades, and prepare users=
 and support teams accordingly.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
08857?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

(Updated) Microsoft Teams: New chat sections for muted and meeting chats

MC1269864 | May 12 - Microsoft Teams will introduce two new chat sections=E2=
=80=94Muted chats (enabled by default) and Meeting chats (disabled by defau=
lt)=E2=80=94to organize conversations. Rollout starts early May 2026, compl=
eting by month-end. Users can enable, disable, or reorder these sections; n=
o admin action or controls are required.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC12=
69864?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

(Updated) Transitioning Teams Android Device Management from Teams admin Ce=
nter to the Teams Rooms Pro Management portal

MC1227622 | May 12 - Teams Android device management is transitioning from =
the Teams admin center to the Teams Rooms Pro Management portal by mid-2026=
. This unifies management of all Teams devices in one portal, enhancing inv=
entory, updates, health monitoring, and remote actions. No immediate action=
 is needed until General Availability.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC12=
27622?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

** Additional updates
---------------------
Microsoft Teams: Digital signage support for Teams panels

MC1311979 | May 15 - Microsoft Teams will support digital signage on idle T=
eams panels starting June 2026, configurable by admins via the Teams Rooms =
Pro Management portal. It supports third-party providers like Appspace and =
XOGO, requires Teams Rooms Pro or Shared Spaces licenses, and allows tenant=
-wide or device-specific settings.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11979?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Classic Outlook for Windows: User-initiated insights with Copilot

MC1311978 | May 15 - Classic Outlook for Windows will add User Initiated In=
sights with Copilot, letting users highlight email text to get contextual A=
I-generated insights. Rolling out May-June 2026, the feature is on by defau=
lt for eligible users, integrates into Outlook without add-ins, and follows=
 existing Microsoft 365 security policies.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11978?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Department billing for Microsoft 365 Backup

MC1311976 | May 15 - Microsoft 365 Backup now supports department billing, =
allowing admins to create up to 50 billing policies by department, geograph=
y, or unit, with delegated control via RBAC. Available to new customers fro=
m mid-May 2026; existing customers will get it later this year with no imme=
diate changes.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11976?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Microsoft Purview compliance portal: Role groups user interface (UI) enhanc=
ements

MC1311975 | May 15 - Microsoft Purview compliance portal is enhancing the R=
ole groups UI to let admins quickly view assignments by role, member, or th=
eir own permissions. Rolling out mid-June to mid-August 2026, this default-=
enabled update improves permission clarity without changing existing assign=
ments or workflows. No action needed.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11975?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

PowerPoint for Windows: Create a presentation with Copilot directly from Po=
werPoint Home

MC1311974 | May 15 - PowerPoint for Windows will enable users with a Copilo=
t license to create presentations directly from PowerPoint Home in the File=
 menu, starting late May 2026. The feature is enabled by default, requires =
no admin changes, and helps users quickly draft presentations using Copilot=
.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11974?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

PowerPoint for Mac: Create a presentation with Copilot directly from PowerP=
oint Home

MC1311973 | May 15 - PowerPoint for Mac will enable users with a Microsoft =
Copilot license to create presentations directly from PowerPoint Home in th=
e File menu, starting late May 2026. The feature is enabled by default, req=
uires no admin changes, and aims to streamline the workflow from idea to dr=
aft.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11973?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

PowerPoint for the web: Create a presentation with Copilot directly from th=
e PowerPoint web app

MC1311972 | May 15 - Starting mid-May 2026, PowerPoint for the web will let=
 users with a Microsoft Copilot license create presentations directly using=
 Copilot. This feature is enabled by default, requires no admin changes, an=
d is immediately available upon opening the app. No action is needed to pre=
pare.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11972?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

Copilot in SharePoint will start rolling out to all tenants as an opt-out p=
review starting in mid-June 2026

MC1311968 | May 15 - Copilot in SharePoint will roll out as an opt-out prev=
iew starting mid-June 2026 for Microsoft 365 Copilot licensed users. It ena=
bles AI-powered content creation and management via a chat interface, respe=
cts user permissions, and offers admin controls for tenant or site-level op=
t-in/out and customization.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC13=
11968?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

(Updated) Microsoft 365 Copilot: Planner Agent rename and rollout to premiu=
m and basic plans

MC1250279 | May 15 - Starting mid-March 2026, the Project Manager agent in =
Microsoft Planner will be renamed Planner Agent, aligning with Microsoft 36=
5 Copilot branding. It will be available to Copilot-licensed users in group=
-based Planner premium and basic plans, with no functional changes. Rollout=
 completes by May 2026; no admin action required.
View more
https://admin.microsoft.com/AdminPortal/home#/MessageCenter/:/messages/MC12=
50279?MCLinkSource=3DDigestMail

